From 19725a84202dfce4412ba8c83ebf6bfa0df84d46 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Harshitha Prem <hprem@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 22 Sep 2025 12:33:59 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL:hostapd: Add MLD support for accept policy

Extend the existing hostapd ACL logic to support Multi-Link Device (MLD)
addresses in addition to link addresses. This enhancement enables APs to
apply ACL policies based on either address type.

For the accept policy, if either the link address or the MLD address is
present in the allowed list, the client association is accepted.

For the deny policy, if either the link address or the MLD address is
present in the deny list, the client association is rejected.

Patch-dependency: None
Patch-work: None

Signed-off-by: Harshitha Prem <hprem@qti.qualcomm.com>
